---
import Layout from '@layouts/Layout.astro';
import { SITE, SOCIALS } from '@lib/constants';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy Policy for Faithfully Crafted -- how we handle your data, third-party services, and your rights."
>
  <article class="py-12 sm:py-16">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 prose prose-sm sm:prose-base">
      <header class="text-center mb-12" data-reveal="up">
        <h1 class="font-heading text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-text">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="mt-3 text-text-muted">Last updated: March 13, 2026</p>
      </header>

      <section data-reveal="up" data-reveal-delay="100">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-text mt-10 mb-4">Introduction</h2>
        <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
          Faithfully Crafted ("we," "us," or "our") operates the website at
          <a href={SITE.url}>{SITE.url}</a>. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use,
          and protect information when you visit our website.
        </p>
        <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed mt-3">
          By using our website, you agree to the practices described in this policy. If you do not
          agree, please do not use the website.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section data-reveal="up">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-text mt-10 mb-4">Information We Collect</h2>
        <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
          We collect information to provide better services to all our users. Collecting this information helps us improve our website and provide a tailored experience. The types of information we collect include:
        </p>
        <h3 class="font-heading text-lg font-bold text-text mt-6 mb-2">Information Automatically Collected</h3>
        <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
          When you access our Site, our servers and third-party hosting providers automatically collect information about your interaction with the Site. This may include:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-text-muted mt-3 space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Device Information:</strong> We may collect device-specific information (such as your hardware model, operating system version, and unique device identifiers).</li>
          <li><strong>Log Information:</strong> Details of how you used our service (such as your search queries), your IP address, browser type, referring/exit pages, and operating system.</li>
          <li><strong>Cookies and Similar Technologies:</strong> Our hosting provider (Cloudflare) may use standard web technologies as part of its service operations. We do not set first-party cookies on this Site.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section data-reveal="up">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-text mt-10 mb-4">Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
          Our website relies on the following third-party services:
        </p>

        <h3 class="font-heading text-lg font-bold text-text mt-6 mb-2">Cloudflare</h3>
        <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
          Our website is hosted on Cloudflare Pages. Cloudflare may collect basic server logs
          (IP addresses, browser type, request timestamps) as part of standard web hosting
          operations. For details, see
          <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Cloudflare's Privacy Policy</a>.
        </p>

        <h3 class="font-heading text-lg font-bold text-text mt-6 mb-2">Social Media Plugins and External Services</h3>
        <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
          Our website displays gallery content sourced from our public Facebook Page via the Facebook Graph API. This content is fetched on our servers at build time and served as static images and text -- no Facebook scripts, tracking pixels, or third-party code runs in your browser when you visit our Site.
          Our website also contains links to our social media profiles. Clicking these links takes you to third-party platforms governed by their own privacy policies:
          <br /><br />
          <a href="https://www.facebook.com/privacy/policy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Meta's Privacy Policy (Facebook and Instagram)</a>
        </p>


      </section>

      <section data-reveal="up">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-text mt-10 mb-4">AI-Powered Customer Support</h2>
        <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
          When you message us on Facebook Messenger, an AI assistant may respond to common questions
          (such as shipping, materials, or lead time) to help you faster. Here is what you should know:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-text-muted mt-3 space-y-2">
          <li>The AI clearly identifies itself as an AI assistant when asked.</li>
          <li>You can request a human at any time by typing "talk to Faith" -- the bot will pause and Faith will reach out personally.</li>
          <li>Your messages are processed by Google's Gemini API to generate the AI's responses.</li>
          <li>The last few messages of your conversation (up to 8) are temporarily stored in Cloudflare KV to maintain context within a single chat session. Stored messages are automatically deleted after 7 days.</li>
          <li>We do not use your messages for AI training or share them with any third party beyond what is necessary to generate a response.</li>
          <li>Faith reviews all orders, custom requests, complaints, and partnership inquiries personally -- the AI never finalizes these.</li>
          <li>The AI never quotes prices and never commits Faith to specific timelines; those are always confirmed by Faith directly.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section data-reveal="up">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-text mt-10 mb-4">External Links</h2>
        <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
          Our website contains links to external websites and services (Facebook, Instagram,
          Messenger). We are not responsible for the privacy practices of these third-party sites.
          We encourage you to review their privacy policies before providing any personal
          information.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section data-reveal="up">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-text mt-10 mb-4">Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
          Our website is not directed at children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly
          collect personal information from children. If you believe a child has provided us
          with personal information, please contact us so we can take appropriate action.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section data-reveal="up">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-text mt-10 mb-4">Data Security</h2>
        <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
          We take reasonable measures to protect any information associated with our website.
          Our site is served over HTTPS with strict security headers, including Content Security
          Policy, HSTS, and X-Frame-Options.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section data-reveal="up">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-text mt-10 mb-4">Your Privacy Rights</h2>
        <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
          Depending on your location and applicable data protection laws (including the GDPR and CCPA), you may have certain rights regarding your personal information, including the right to:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-text-muted mt-3 space-y-2">
          <li>Request access to your personal information.</li>
          <li>Request correction or deletion of your personal information.</li>
          <li>Object to or restrict our processing of your personal information.</li>
          <li>Request portability of your personal information.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed mt-3">
          To exercise any of these rights, please contact us using the information provided below. We will respond to your request in accordance with applicable legal requirements.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section data-reveal="up">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-text mt-10 mb-4">Data Retention</h2>
        <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
          We retain personal information we collect from you where we have an ongoing legitimate business need to do so (for example, to provide you with a service you have requested or to comply with applicable legal, tax, or accounting requirements). When we have no ongoing legitimate business need to process your personal information, we will either delete or anonymize it.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section data-reveal="up">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-text mt-10 mb-4">Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
          We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time in response to changing legal, technical, or business developments. When we update our Privacy Policy, we will take appropriate measures to inform you, consistent with the significance of the changes we make. You can see when this Privacy Policy was last updated by checking the "Last updated" date displayed at the top of this Privacy Policy.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section data-reveal="up">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-text mt-10 mb-4">Contact Us</h2>
        <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
          If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, you can reach us at:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-none text-text-muted mt-3 space-y-1">
          <li>Email: <a href={`mailto:${SITE.email}`}>{SITE.email}</a></li>
          <li>Facebook: <a href={SOCIALS.facebook.url} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Our Facebook Page</a></li>
          <li>Instagram: <a href={SOCIALS.instagram.url} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Our Instagram Profile</a></li>
        </ul>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
